]},{"name":"Isabelle","meanings":["form of   Isabel  , now in frequent use in the English-speaking world."]},{"name":"Isobella","meanings":["form of   Isabel  , which has been popular in England since the 18th century and has recently become the preferred form of the name."]},{"name":"Isobelle","meanings":["Originally a Spanish version of   Elizabeth  , which was coined by deletion of the first syllable and alteration of the final consonant sound to one that can normally end a word in Spanish. The name was imported into France in the early Middle Ages, and thence into England. It was a royal name, and its enduring popularity may have been enhanced by the fact that it was borne by a queen of England—  Isabella  (  1296–1358 ), daughter of  Philip IV  of France—even though she led a turbulent life and eventually had her husband,  Edward II , murdered."]},{"name":"Isobel","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Isabel ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Isabel Brehaugh was born in 1424 as the daughter of William Brehaugh. She married Richard Thorold jr in 1444, in Selby, Yorkshire, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died in 1468, in England, United Kingdom, at the age of 44."},"et":{"1424–1468":"1424–1468","1430–1460":"1430–1460","1444–1538":"1444–1538","1410–Male":"1410–Surnud","1424":"1424","1468":"1468","1444":"1444","1410":"1410","1430":"1430","1460":"1460","1538":"1538","Thornham Magna, Suffolk, England":"Thornham Magna, Suffolk, England","Selby and Hough, Yorkshire, England":"Selby, Yorkshire, England",", , , England, United Kingdom":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Selby, Yorkshire, England":"Selby, Yorkshire, England"},"fi":{"1424–1468":"1424–1468","1430–1460":"1430–1460","1444–1538":"1444–1538","1410–Male":"1410–Kuollut","1424":"1424","1468":"1468","1444":"1444","1410":"1410","1430":"1430","1460":"1460","1538":"1538","Thornham Magna, Suffolk, England":"Thornham Magna, Suffolk, England","Selby and Hough, Yorkshire, England":"Selby, Yorkshire, England",", , , Engla